ATHENS , May 7 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- A military crisis-containment exercise codenamed `` Athena ` 96 '' will be held in Athens on May 13-17 within the framework of the partnership for peace , the country 's National Defense Ministry announced today .
<ENAMEX TYPE="OKAY">Taking part in the exercise will be military officers and Foreign Ministry officials from Albania , Bulgaria , Greece , Italy , Spain , Romania , the United Kingdom and the United States .</ENAMEX>
In addition , observers have been invited from NATO .
The announcement said the exercise aims at exchanging views and creating a common perception on matters pertaining to the handling of crises , with discussions and meetings during an imaginary , simulated crisis .
